Sentiment Intensity Analysis

By using SentimentIntensityAnalyzer from nltk, I calculated the sentiment intensity of each Tweet text as well as the average sentiment intensity across the corpus. By looking at the mean sentiment intensity of the corpus, it seems that people’s attitude are mainly neutral when they Tweet about East Asia’s fertility. The compound score is the sum of positive, negative & neutral scores which is then normalized between -1(most extreme negative) and +1 (most extreme positive).

  • negative: 0.138251
  • positive: 0.06674
  • neutral: 0.789498
  • compound: -0.147502
